// This is 'Ruckard Scalping 02' strategy. It is written using 'Zignaly Tutorial' strategy as a base.
//
// 
// It was originally tested at LTCUSDT pair, 1m (1 minute) timeframe and 75x leverage.
// The strategy applies many substrats.
// [B]Substrat 01 (SS01)[/B] : We apply 8 DCAs levels:
// [LIST]
// [*] DCA Level 1: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage1=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage1=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 2: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage2=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage2=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 3: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage3=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage3=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 4: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage4=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage4=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 5: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage5=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage5=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 6: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage6=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage6=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 7: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage7=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage7=50) is rebought.
// [*] DCA Level 8: When price is 0.40% different (in opposite direction to the position side) to position price (DCATargetPercentage8=0.40) then 50% of the position (DCAAmountPercentage8=50) is rebought.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 02 (SS02)[/B] : Adjusted TakeProfit levels when too many DCAs are triggered:
// [LIST]
// [*] DCA Level 4: TakeProfit is set to 0.20%.
// [*] DCA Level 5: TakeProfit is set to 0.15%.
// [*] DCA Level 6: TakeProfit is set to 0.10%.
// [*] DCA Level 7: TakeProfit is set to 0.08%.
// [*] DCA Level 8: TakeProfit is set to 0.05%.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 03 (SS03)[/B] : Too fast high DCAs close the position.
// [LIST]
// [*] If we are in DCA Level 4 (or higher) and two DCA levels are triggered in less than 2 minutes then the position is exited.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 04 (SS04)[/B] : 0.20 USDT initial real investment
// [LIST]
// [*] 0.20 USDT initial real investment
// [*] At 75x leverage that means 15 USDT investment.
// [*] So that 50% of it can be rebought ( 7.5 USDT) because that's higher than the minimum in Binance (5 USDT).
// [*] That also means the strategy needs to manage its capital internally to meet this requirement.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 05 (SS05)[/B] : Start date and hour setting.
// [B]Substrat 06 (SS06)[/B] : Use 'TradingView only' integration as much as possible. Final stop loss should be hybrid though.
// [B]Substrat 07 (SS07)[/B] : Both long and short sides are supported.
// [B]Substrat 08 (SS08)[/B] : (Optional). If last position ends in breakeven we should wait 15 minutes, 30 minutes, 45 minutes, 60 minutes, 75 minutes and finally 100 minutes. This needs to be managed per side and reset when there is not a breakeven or the side is changed.
// [B]Substrat 09 (SS09)[/B] : If the strategy detects an opposite side opportunity the current side is not closed as it happens with the default Zignaly strategy. That way we might avoid false price direction changes.
// [B]Substrat 10 (SS10)[/B] : If 4 DCAs have been triggered and price is greater than 0.80% then an stop loss is set to positive 0.20% (as a breakeven).
// [B]Substrat 11 (SS11)[/B] : (Optional) If position price is not 0.30% greater than EMA30 in less than 60 minutes and no Trailing Stop is on then exit the position.
// [B]Substrat 12 (SS12)[/B] : Which side a position should have is based on latest 30 periods.
// [LIST]
// [*] If candle maximums are higher and candle minimums are higher then we go long.
// [*] If candle minimums are lower and candle maximums are lower then we go short.
// [*] If it's mixed we don't open new positions.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 13 (SS13)[/B] : Wait for a 20% retracement on the latest 30 period range before entering the position. Recalculate on each new period if position is not open yet.
// Example:
// [LIST]
// [*] Last 30 periods maximum: 171.84.
// [*] Last 30 periods minimum: 169.79.
// [*] Last 30 periods indicate short position.
// [*] Minimum to maximum distance: 171.84 - 169.79 = 2.05
// [*] Short minimal price: 169.79 + (2.05*(20/100)) = 170.20
// [*] That means that you can start the short position at 170.20 but you cannot start the short position at 170.19.
// [/LIST]
// [B]Substrat 14 (SS14)[/B] : -0.60% failsafe stop loss (when DCAs are not triggered fast enough or there are no DCAs left).
// [B]Substrat 15 (SS15)[/B] : Mode A (default): Trailing stop trigger at 1.10% and 0.70% distance.
//
// [B]SETTINGS[/B]
// [B]__ SETTINGS - Capital[/B]
// [LIST]
// [*] (CAPITAL) Capital quote invested per order in USDT units {100.0}. This setting is only used when '(ZIG) Provider type' is set to 'Signal Provider'.
// [*] (CAPITAL) Capital percentage invested per order (%) {25.0}. This setting is only used when '(ZIG) Provider type' is set to 'Copy Trader Provider'.
// [/LIST]
